                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00114A Pacific War/503: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harrison</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-06-16">June 16,
                            1943</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1479. American interests—Japan. Domei<note n="72" xml:id="d868fn72">Japanese
                        official news agency.</note> has reported that punishment has been meted out
                    by Japanese to 25 members American armed forces who have recently revealed their
                    identity after being held as civilians in the Philippines. Request Swiss
                    authorities to endeavor to verify this report, to obtain names of men, and to
                    report the nature of the punishment.<note n="73" xml:id="d868fn73">In telegram
                        No. 7544, December 1, the Minister in Switzerland reported that the Swiss
                        Legation in Tokyo verified the report that 25 soldiers interned at Santo
                        Tomas were condemned to 2 months’ imprisonment for offense as stated and
                        interned in POW camp in the Philippines after serving sentences
                        (711.11B114A/121).</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
